#: ../../../sound/designs/oss-emulation.rst:224
msgid ""
"Since ALSA has completely different mixer interface, the emulation of OSS "
"mixer is relatively complicated.  ALSA builds up a mixer element from "
"several different ALSA (mixer) controls based on the name string.  For "
"example, the volume element SOUND_MIXER_PCM is composed from \"PCM Playback "
"Volume\" and \"PCM Playback Switch\" controls for the playback direction and "
"from \"PCM Capture Volume\" and \"PCM Capture Switch\" for the capture "
"directory (if exists).  When the PCM volume of OSS is changed, all the "
"volume and switch controls above are adjusted automatically."
msgstr ""

